# Quick Markdown Lint Verification Commands

Run these BEFORE committing markdown files:

## 1. Check blanks around code blocks (MD031)
grep -n "^[^ ]" *.md | grep -B1 "\`\`\`"

## 2. Check line length (>100 chars)
awk 'length > 100 && !/^https/ && !/^|/ {print NR": " length($0) " chars"}' *.md

## 3. Check for invalid file:// links
grep -n 'file://' *.md

## 4. Check heading hierarchy
grep '^#' *.md | head -10

## 5. Check unclosed code blocks
awk '/^```/{count++} END {if(count%2) print "UNCLOSED CODE BLOCKS FOUND"}' *.md

## Auto-fix script
bash scripts/fix-markdown-warnings.sh

## Full check (all 5 checks):
echo "=== MD031 Check ===" && grep -n "^[^ ]" *.md | grep -B1 "\`\`\`" && echo "✓ PASS" || echo "❌ FAIL"
echo "=== Line Length Check ===" && awk 'length > 100 && !/^https/ && !/^|/ {print NR": " length}' *.md && echo "❌ FAIL" || echo "✓ PASS"
echo "=== file:// Check ===" && grep -n 'file://' *.md && echo "❌ FAIL" || echo "✓ PASS"

See MARKDOWN_CONVENTIONS.md for detailed rules and IDE setup.
